Our field2D swervePoseEstimator is not matching our robot’s movements - we negated our getYaw, to switch from CW+ to CCW+, and changed some motor inversions to fix the rotation, but now the Y translation is inverted on our field 2d on shuffleboard after turning 90 degrees - so going backwards moves us forwards in the odometry but not on the real robot.

Our Github for this project

Any insights are greatly apricated

Can you be more descriptive of the problem? Is it just the y or also the x? If its both, In your SwerveModule’s getPosition you may have to multiply your distance by -1. My team had to do that.
